comment.body:
> I don't want two separate manually maintained copies, 

I hear you.

> . . . so we'd probably need a script to generate the .dox version from the .md version... yuck.

 Yeah, you're probably right here...

> We now have https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs-rust 

Great, thanks! Indeed, it builds fine. Though I have two issues with it:
1. It is unclear how to make `liboqs-rust` bind to an existing installation of `liboqs`, instead of building its own copy.
2. `cargo test` fails exactly the same way (with stack overflow) as https://github.com/thomwiggers/oqs-rs.git . I've submitted a report here https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs-rust/issues/142

issue.title: Fix SIKE exports in DLL
issue.body:
Following the discussion in #1222, this PR addresses the SIKE functions export issue, by introducing a new directive `set(CMAKE_WINDOWS_EXPORT_ALL_SYMBOLS ON)` in the CMakeLists.txt file.

<!-- Please answer the following questions to help manage version and changes across projects. -->

* [no] Does this PR change the input/output behaviour of a cryptographic algorithm (i.e., does it change known answer test values)?  (If so, a version bump will be required from *x.y.z* to *x.(y+1).0*.)
* [no] Does this PR change the the list of algorithms available -- either adding, removing, or renaming?  (If so, PRs in OQS-OpenSSL, OQS-BoringSSL, and OQS-OpenSSH will also be required by the time this is merged.)

<!-- Once your pull request is ready for review and passing continuous integration tests, please convert from a draft PR to a normal PR, and request a review from one of the OQS core team members. -->

comment.body:
> Is there something in the SIKE code where OQS_API is not being properly attached to the missing SIKE functions?

At first glance, no: All SIKE APIs are "adorned" in the same way as the properly exported SIDH functions. A bit of a mystery...

> The impact on the DLL feels like a big change, 

Completely agree. So then I would suggest closing this PR without merge, add a comment pointing to this `cmake`variable in https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/wiki/Platform-specific-notes-for-building-liboqs#building-on-windows as a "workaround" and leave #1222 unresolved until the SIKE symbols get properly exported. OK for everyone?
Good opportunity to also resolve the "missing symbols in Windows" mystery (discussed in #1224) at the same time?
